flowRoot.flowPara: A server manages the resources of a network, without it your network is in danger. The server is the heart of your network! Use the server to create buildings, troops, and resources.
Software Updaters are buildings you create to unlock other troops not available to you yet. They are costly to build because they take quite a bit of time!
Algorithms are step by step procedures. Most network attacks are algorithms. Use the Algorithm Factory to create attack troops, these troops represent network attacks (see below).
A database is a resource that stores data and using a database is the most efficient way to store a lot of data. In the game, it will allow you to hold more troops in a location.

A firewall secures a network by blocking outsiders who are not authorized to enter your network. It controls what comes in and what leaves a network. Use firewall to block those pesky enemy troops coming from the school to attack you.
RSA is a public-key cryptography. Think of it as sending a secret message without an unintended audience seeing it.
Use RSA to Encrypt(hide) your troop so the enemy will not see or attack it. When you Encrypt a troop it becomes disabled. Decrypt (unhide) the troop to enable it and use it.
A sinkhole gives false information to try to prevent others from accessing resources in your network. Use sinkhole to prevent enemy troops from entering a location.
